      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "@MarcoFalke looks like `float` is only supported on tables and images according to http://doc.qt.io/archives/qt-4.8/richtext-html-subset.html#css-properties . If the individual lines were wrapped in `p` or `div`, `align=right` should work, although the cleanest version would probably be to convert the dialog to use `<table>`. At some point, I might try to implement this, but don't hold your breath :-) (also, I'm very happy if someone beats me to it!)",
